1 An Act to amend provisions pertaining to the timing of municipal elections.
2 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
3 Section 1. That § 9-1-1 be AMENDED:
4 9-1-1. Terms used in this title, unless the context otherwise plainly requires,
5 mean:
6 (1) "County," the county or counties where a municipality is located;
7 (2) "Governing body," the board of trustees, the board of commissioners, or the
8 common council of a municipality;
9 (3) "Lot" includes parcel or tract of land;
10 (4) "Municipal corporation" or "municipality," any city or town that is organized
11 pursuant to this title;
12 (5) "Owner," the grantee in the last deed of conveyance of any lot or parcel of land
13 recorded in the office of the register of deeds of the county or counties in which
14 the municipality is located, or the heirs or successors to the grantee; and
15 (6) "Publish," publication in an official newspaper of the municipality as designated by
16 the governing body pursuant to § 9-12-6; and
17 (7) "Regular election," the municipal election held pursuant to § 9-13-1 or section 19
18 of this Act.
